  "merger_description": "Sapphire Cattle Company, an entity within the Hewitt group (**Hewitt**) is proposing to acquire Nolan Meats Pty Ltd (**Nolan Meats**), including land and assets, via connected entities (the\u00a0**Acquisition**).\n\nHewitt is a majority-owned subsidiary of the Public Sector Pension Investment Board (**PSP Investments**), an investment management fund established by the Parliament of Canada. The remaining shares in Hewitt are owned by the Hewitt family.\n\nHewitt is a red meat producer, headquartered in Brisbane, which farms cattle and sheep, undertakes secondary processing of beef into value-added products (such as beef patties), and distributes (including the\u00a0packaging, marketing and sale of) beef to supermarkets, the food service industry, butchers and international customers. Hewitt predominantly produces organic beef products.\n\nNolan Meats is a beef producer headquartered in Gympie, Queensland, which undertakes lot feeding of cattle, primary processing of cattle, and the wholesale distribution (including\u00a0packaging, marketing and sale) of beef to supermarkets, the food service industry, butchers and international customers. Nolan Meats\u2019 core assets include a primary processing facility with an annual capacity of 260,000 head of cattle, located in Gympie, and a 4,000 standard cattle unit-licensed beef cattle feedlot situated 65 kilometres west of the processing facility.",
